The scores of PSQI, AIS, and VAS are presented in Table1
. Compared to non-FMW, FMW had significantly higher scores of PSQI (9.3±3.8 vs 7.5±3.7; P<0.001; Cohen's d =0.47), AIS (6.9±4.3 vs 5.3±3.8; P<0.001; Cohen's d=0.38), anxiety (4.9±2.7 vs 4.3±2.6; P<0.001; Cohen's d=0.22), and depression (4.1±2.5 vs 3.6±2.4; P=0.001; Cohen's d=0.21) (Figure 1
).
